HEADWORD: Lixivium
<hw>Lix*iv"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lixivium</ets>, <ets>lixivia</ets>. See <er>Lixivial</er>.]</ety>
<def>A solution of alkaline salts extracted from wood ashes; hence, any
solution obtained by lixiviation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

